<content type="str">SOUTH HOLLAND â€“ Illinois State Police said a $1,000 reward is available for information leading to the arrest of a suspect wanted attacking a trooper in the southern Chicago suburbs. 
   
State police said the plain-clothes trooper was in an unmarked squad car trying to question someone at a toll plaza on Interstate 294 in South Holland on Nov. 7. Police said the suspect approached the trooper with a handgun when the trooper identified himself as a police officer. Police said there was a struggle over the gun and the offender fired at least one bullet before fleeing. 
 
The officer wasn&apos;t shot but was hurt and still is recovering from injuries. 
 
